<paragraph id="8BCEFC30FFC4967FFF6B5DB9FCBC88C3" blockId="2.[178,1085,395,475]" pageId="2" pageNumber="303">
C o m m e n t: The distribution of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7187B3FFC4967FFDF25DB9FD7C88B8" authorityName="ASSING" authorityYear="2014" box="[555,702,395,416]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Nazeris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="303" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tenuipennis">
<emphasis id="B9052022FFC4967FFDF25DB9FD7C88B8" box="[555,702,395,416]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="303">N. tenuipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
includes both the Annapurna and the Manaslu ranges; for a map see 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE081C1FFC4967FFE375D9AFD5688A6" author="ASSING V" box="[494,660,424,446]" pageId="2" pageNumber="303" pagination="65 - 130" refId="ref8180" refString="ASSING V. (2014 b): A revision of the Nazeris fauna of the Himalaya (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Paederinae). - Stuttgarter Beitrage zur Naturkunde A, Neue Serie 7: 65 - 130." type="journal article" year="2014">ASSING (2014b)</bibRefCitation>
. The labels attached to the above material collected by J. Schmidt are identical to those of some of the 
<typeStatus id="54CA4292FFC4967FFCCC5DF4FCBB88C3" box="[789,889,454,475]" pageId="2" pageNumber="303">paratypes</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
